metadata.name: Perspective #33
metadata.description:
A few primitives and a lot of points.

Warning: This piece is GPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices.

Keys
s: Take a screenshot
space: Pause/Play the animation.
r: Play a new animation
↑: Increase point alpha
↓: Decrease point alpha
→: Increase point density
←: Decrease point density

URL Params
w: Width of the canvas - (ex, w=1024) - [0-2048]
h: Height of the canvas - (ex, h=1024) - [0-2048]
a: To set the alpha for the points - [0.0-1.0]
p: To set the total number of points to draw (in millions) [1-8]
s: Make the visual static - (ex, s=1)

metadata.name: Ersbla #373
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: Labyrinth #143
metadata.description:
The beginning of life is an incessant dream, a kaleidoscope of surprising discoveries, a colorful labyrinth in which you are enclosed by indefinitely high walls or a void, which you have to pass on your own. The person who may later become a guide through the labyrinth is still hiding behind some wall, past another turn. The main goal is to find him. If you succeed...


But you will succeed.


© Victoria Crux, 2022

metadata.name: Retrospect #72
metadata.description:
If it were possible, would you do things differently in retrospect?

A continuation of the exploration of the tension between freedom of choice and fate. Are the decisions we make imperfect, yet beautiful, or are they perfect, yet not beautiful?

meezwhite × July 19, 2022


To give the final result a slight retro feel, it is purposefully fuzzified and a filter layer of carefully picked 70s colors is mixed in. 

Click, tap or press [X] to invert colors.

License:
See LICENSE.md

This project uses p5.js.
